<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,760,525,945]" box="[144,256,525,546]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[144,256,525,546]" fontSize="9" level="5" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,256,525,546]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,760,525,945]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
Sparsely pilose species, with head smooth and shiny (except 
<taxonomicName box="[231,343,587,608]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Heraeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,343,587,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[350,436,587,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); ocelli located posteriorly to an imaginary line passing the posterior border of eyes; posterior pronotal lobe and clavus uniformly coloured; corium without pale spots, at most with a small spot restricted to costal margin; evaporative area short, distance from dorsal margin of auricle to dorsal margin of evaporative area shorter than distance from dorsal margin of evaporative area to dorsal margin of metapleura; males with strongly incrassate profemora with one ventral spine much larger than the others and protibiae with a row of small tubercles on inner surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
